body:
I think it's ready for checkin or at least review. 

PS: sieves.py takes about 3 seconds to compile when FlowControl is compiled and about 7 when not.
Some tests fails some are not correct and some should be fixed

commit.message: NameNode: add control flow hint flags
Buffer support for uninitialized NULL variables
Set init_to_none flag to False
Fix locals()
Update locals test
Do XDECREF when init_to_none is 0 or False
speed up flow control implementation by compiling it
Update deletion test
Add control flow directives
Add control flow stuff from vitek/unitialized
Add control flow testcases
Move star_arg and starstar_arg to FuncDefNode
Add generators support
Oops add rhs for SingleAssignmentNode
Add handler for unhandled AssignmentNode
Add support for with statement
Add CreateControlFlowGraph to the compile pipeline
Add extra empty lines to follow PEP8
Use cf prefix for control-flow related members
Handle allow_null flag
Don't issue error or warning for arrays and buffers
Remove DelStatNode hack
Remove tabs
Add testcase for closure variable deletion
Remove with test
Add some more CF tests
Add CF testcases for generators and with statement
Add failing testcase
Chain exception in finally clause
Add extra with test
Don't track arrays and c-structs/unions
Buffer is normal object, remove workaround
Fix finally inside/outside the loop
NameNode.generate_deletion_code use cf-hints
Add cf_state member, probably not the best place for it
Remove for-from variable hack
Initialize node.cf_state to empty set
Update control-flow stuff and setup hints
Oops remove debug printing
Fix cf problem with loops inside else clause of another one loop
CF: fix locals_expressions_T430 issue
Warn on non-pyobject unbound variables
Mark node as terminator if no control-flow node
If no parents don't make next block current
add some more unreachable code tests
Run RemoveUnreachableCode one more time after control flow analysis
Speedup flow-control by using big-integer bitsets instead of native python sets
Compile FlowControl module
Fix after cythonizing
Add some simple run tests for control-flow

Disable flow-control compilation for CPython < 2.5
As it doesn't have builtin sets.
Add testcase for local variable deletion
Mark unblound local variable as "unlikely" case
Move message reporting to MessageCollection
Completely remove init_to_none attribute
Initiazile pyobject entries to NULL by default
add some more runtime tests for closures, nested functions and classes
Fix control-flow and closure entries
Don't initialize scoped locals to None
Track closure variables too
Make UnboundLocalError message same as in CPython
Raise correct exception if entry came from closure
Run uninitialized test in both cpython and cython
Uninitialized test Py3k fix
Fix bufaccess tests broken by CF
Fix tests broken by CF
Add utility for unbound locals exception and use it inside CCodeWriter.put_error_if_unbound
Don't use print() inside w_unitialized_py3 test, that doesn't work for python < 2.6

title: control flow
